{{Quote|Have you ever seen the holopainting of our beloved Emperor with his hand held high, receiving the adulation of a huge crowd? Yes, that's right, ''Palpatine Triumphant''. That was mine. It made me famous on Coruscant.|Venthan Chassu|<ref name="SWG:AED">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>}}
'''''Palpatine Triumphant''''' was the last [[Painting/Legends|piece]] of art made by [[Venthan Chassu/Legends|Venthan Chassu]] before his [[Death/Legends|death]]. It depicted a glorified, maniacal [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] sitting on a throne made out of the cracked bones of various [[Species/Legends|species]].

Even Chassu's biggest admirers were unable to discern what meaning, if any, it had.

==Behind the scenes==
In the [[Wikipedia:MMORPG|MMORPG]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', Venthan Chassu presents a rather different description of ''Palpatine Triumphant''. In the game, Chassu states that ''Palpatine Triumphant'' was a [[Holopainting/Legends|holopainting]] of Palpatine with his hand held high, receiving the adulation of a huge crowd. Therefore, it is not entirely clear which description is more accurate. However, it is possible that both descriptions could harmoniously blend together.

